<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-11-21T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-11-21T09:00:00-05:00" n="182" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860p.512 Residence/7: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-11-21T16:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">November 21,
                                        1928—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 21—11:15
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>94. Would appreciate an immediate telegraphic reply to my urgent despatch
                            No. 5601 of October 3rd, submitting proposal which would eliminate
                            residence tax on American citizens in Latvia. Consulate reports that
                            failure to settle the matter is causing serious inconvenience to
                            American citizens here.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sussdorff</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>